    "intro": "Erigeron abyssinicus, also known as Abyssinian fleabane, is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family that is native to tropical Africa. The plant has been traditionally used for its medicinal properties, which include its anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant effects, contributing to its potential health benefits in treating various conditions such as wounds, respiratory issues, and gastrointestinal problems. The bioactive constituents of Erigeron abyssinicus include sesquiterpene lactones, flavonoids, and phenolic acids, which are responsible for its therapeutic properties. The most common herbal preparations made with Erigeron abyssinicus include teas, infusions, and tinctures, which are used to harness its medicinal benefits."
